{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop automatically classifying people as \u201cBritish by descent\u201d without consent",
        "additional_details": "From 25 February, those holding British citizenship, including any classified by \u201cBritish by descent\u201d, must travel to UK on a UK passport (cost around \u00a3100), renounce their citizenship (even if they never wanted it) costing \u00a3482, or obtain a \u201ccertificate of entitlement\u201d costing \u00a3589. We view these as a financial penalty for those classified as British against their wishes. The rules apply to people just transiting through the UK, whereas non-Brits only require an ETA costing \u00a316.",
        "background": "Stop automatically classifying people born abroad as \u201cBritish by descent\u201d if they have a British parent. They should retain their entitlement to hold British citizenship as at present, but this should be through their active choice and application, rather than being automatic without their consent.",
